.SH NAME
bu \- program to backup files and directories.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bu
.RI [-hv ] "FILE1 [FILE2, FILE3, ...]" ...
.br
.B bar
.RI [ options ] " files" ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
This manual page documents briefly the functions of the bu utility.
.B bu
and
.B bar
commands.
.PP
.\" TeX users may be more comfortable with the \fB<whatever>\fP and
.\" \fI<whatever>\fP escape sequences to invode bold face and italics, 
.\" respectively.
\fBbu\fP is a program that back's up files and directories using timestamps and bzips them.
.SH OPTIONS
